<item>
            <title>[SOLR-8199] Text specifying which UI a user is looking at is incorrect</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8199</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the top right corner of the admin UI, a text is available to indicate whether the user is looking at the original UI or the new one.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But it currently says &quot;New UI&quot; for &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8983/solr/#/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8983/solr/#/&lt;/a&gt; and &quot;Original UI&quot; for &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8983/solr/index.html#/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8983/solr/index.html#/&lt;/a&gt; when it should be the other way around.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue is tied to #&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7666&quot; title=&quot;Umbrella ticket for Angular JS post-5.2.1 issues&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-7666&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-7666&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
