                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14972661" author="ychaker" created="Sat, 24 Oct 2015 15:46:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Original UI with the &quot;New UI&quot; text&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14972662" author="ychaker" created="Sat, 24 Oct 2015 15:47:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New Admin UI with the &quot;Original UI&quot; text&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14972735" author="upayavira" created="Sat, 24 Oct 2015 17:12:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Those &quot;new UI&quot; and &quot;Original UI&quot; are supposed to be &lt;b&gt;links&lt;/b&gt; rather than &lt;b&gt;titles&lt;/b&gt;. From your original confusion I took the fact that that wasn&apos;t clear.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please do an SVN up, and redo &apos;ant server&apos; - you&apos;ll see I&apos;ve added a warning message on the new UI (as a part of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7858&quot; title=&quot;Make Angular UI default&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-7858&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-7858&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;). Let me know what you think - is it clearer now? Other suggestions as to how to make it clear that the &quot;New UI&quot; words are a link not a title?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14972760" author="ychaker" created="Sat, 24 Oct 2015 17:33:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The new message on the new UI is definitely much better.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For the link on the old UI, how about something like this: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&quot;Try the New UI&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;Switch to the New UI&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;Go to the New UI&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
&quot;Feeling bold? Check out the new UI here&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anything with a verb (call to action) would indicate that this is a link instead of a title, so that would be a fist step towards making it clearer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I want to suggest some CSS/UI improvements like adding an underline or something to it to make it look like a link, but there is nothing else on that page that would give a visual queue to the user that an underline means link because there aren&apos;t any like that on the page.&lt;br/&gt;
The only similar links are in the footer (documentation,  issue tracker, etc). So maybe adding an icon (eg. right arrow -&amp;gt;) next to it and making it the same style (on hover) like the footer links.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14972770" author="upayavira" created="Sat, 24 Oct 2015 17:48:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;All good suggestions. Wanna have a go at a patch?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Edit files in server/solr-webapp/webapp. They should then show up in your browser immediately.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You will need to copy the changed files over to webapp/web, then do svn diff &amp;gt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-8199&quot; title=&quot;Text specifying which UI a user is looking at is incorrect&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-8199&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-8199&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.patch and then attach that file to this issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you just want to keep looking for other issues, that&apos;s fine too &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
